# Project Standards & Best Practices

## Comments & docs

- Write code comments, readme, specs and changelogs in English only, even if the user communicates in another language.

## Dependencies

- Add new dependencies only if absolutely necessary. Always ask user about adding packages.

## Pull Requests & Commits

- Write clear, descriptive commit messages in English. Each pull request should contain only related changes and be reviewed by at least one team member.

## Sensitive Data

- Never commit secrets, passwords, or API keys to the repository. Use environment variables and `.env` files, and ensure they are listed in `.gitignore`.

## Documentation

- Update documentation (`README.md`, code comments, etc.) when adding new features or making significant changes. Do not write changelogs in README.md. There is CHANGELOG.md for that purpose.
- Update CHANGELOG.md when adding new features or making significant changes.

## Tests
- Update integration tests always for new changes made
- Write new tests only for new functionality and methods
